      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SCHUHBECK (2) will find this a lot easier than what he's been racing in, beaten 3.8L last time out at Pinjarra. Back to this class looks a big tick and the inside draw should see him on the speed. Ticks plenty of boxes and will take plenty of catching. FOUR SEAS (1) is better than she showed last time out at Albany, beaten a long way after a strong effort at Esperance two starts ago. Cheung's claim is a bonus and he'll be poised to strike in the small field. Tongue tie goes on now and she can make a statement. NO SECOND THOUGHTS (3) finished 18 lengths adrift in 11th at Belmont Park over 1200m at her latest appearance. The small field will suit her racing pattern. Sure to be prominent. I'M THAT GIRL (4) last appeared four weeks ago when she was beaten 5.5 lengths into third over 1250m at Kojonup. Not out of the question due to a scarcity of opponents.",
